{"id":"4bf1f54dc1ff251b54d23a2e3688f7830c2cb387","axis":"silent","repo":"microsoft/vscode","sha":"4bf1f54dc1ff251b54d23a2e3688f7830c2cb387","parsed":{"files":[{"path":"src/vs/platform/agentHost/node/agentPluginManager.ts","lines":["@@ -24,12 +24,22 @@ interface ICacheEntry {","  * Implementation of {@link IAgentPluginManager}.","  *","  * Syncs plugin directories to local storage under","- * `{userDataPath}/agentPlugins/{key}/`. Uses a {@link SequencerByKey}","- * per plugin URI so that concurrent syncs of the same plugin are","- * serialized and cannot clobber each other.","+ * `{userDataPath}/agentPlugins/{key}/{nonce}/`. Materializing each nonce in","+ * its own subdirectory means a new revision is copied into a fresh directory","+ * rather than overwriting (and deleting) the previous one. This both avoids","+ * `EBUSY` failures when the in-use copy is still locked and allows multiple","+ * revisions of the same plugin to coexist — e.g. a long-running session may","+ * still reference an older nonce that we cannot delete yet. Uses a","+ * {@link SequencerByKey} per plugin URI so that concurrent syncs of the same","+ * plugin are serialized and cannot clobber each other.","  *","- * The nonce cache and LRU order are persisted to a JSON file in the","- * base path so they survive process restarts.","+ * Older nonces of a plugin are evicted opportunistically: when the manager","+ * starts up and again after each fresh sync of the same plugin. If a stale","+ * nonce directory cannot be removed (e.g. it is still locked), it is retained","+ * in the LRU and retried on a later cleanup pass.","+ *","+ * The LRU (which records each plugin's URI and nonce) is persisted to a JSON","+ * file in the base path so it survives process restarts.","  */"," export class AgentPluginManager implements IAgentPluginManager {"," \tdeclare readonly _serviceBrand: undefined;","@@ -41,11 +51,12 @@ export class AgentPluginManager implements IAgentPluginManager {"," \t/** Serializes concurrent sync operations per plugin URI. */"," \tprivate readonly _sequencer = new SequencerByKey<string>();"," ","-\t/** Nonces for plugins on disk, keyed by original customization URI string. */","-\tprivate readonly _cachedNonces = new Map<string, string>();","-","-\t/** LRU order: most recently used original customization URI strings at the end. */","-\tprivate readonly _lruOrder: string[] = [];","+\t/**","+\t * LRU of synced plugins, most recently used at the end. Each entry records","+\t * the plugin's original customization URI and the nonce materialized on","+\t * disk under `{key}/{nonce}`.","+\t */","+\tprivate readonly _lru: ICacheEntry[] = [];"," "," \t/** Whether the on-disk cache has been loaded. */"," \tprivate _cacheLoaded = false;","@@ -96,17 +107,20 @@ export class AgentPluginManager implements IAgentPluginManager {"," \t// ---- plugin storage logic -----------------------------------------------"," "," \t/**","-\t * Syncs a single plugin to local storage. Skips the copy when the","-\t * nonce matches the cached value. Returns the local directory URI.","+\t * Syncs a single plugin to local storage. Each nonce is materialized in its","+\t * own `{key}/{nonce}` subdirectory; when the same nonce is already present","+\t * the copy is skipped. After a fresh copy, older nonces of the same plugin","+\t * are evicted on a best-effort basis (retained in the LRU if still locked).","+\t * Returns the local directory URI."," \t */"," \tprivate async _syncPlugin(clientId: string, ref: ClientPluginCustomization): Promise<URI> {"," \t\tconst pluginUri = toAgentClientUri(URI.parse(ref.uri), clientId);","-\t\tconst key = this._keyForUri(ref.uri);","-\t\tconst destDir = URI.joinPath(this._basePath, key);","+\t\tconst destDir = this._dirFor(ref.uri, ref.nonce);"," ","-\t\t// Nonce cache hit — skip copy","-\t\tif (ref.nonce && this._cachedNonces.get(ref.uri) === ref.nonce) {","-\t\t\tthis._touchLru(ref.uri);","+\t\t// Nonce cache hit — the plugin is already materialized under the nonce","+\t\t// subdirectory, so skip the copy.","+\t\tif (ref.nonce && this._findEntry(ref.uri, ref.nonce) && await this._fileService.exists(destDir)) {","+\t\t\tthis._touchLru(ref.uri, ref.nonce);"," \t\t\tthis._logService.trace(`[AgentPluginManager] Nonce match for ${ref.uri}, skipping copy`);"," \t\t\treturn destDir;"," \t\t}","@@ -115,10 +129,12 @@ export class AgentPluginManager implements IAgentPluginManager {"," "," \t\tawait this._fileService.copy(pluginUri, destDir, true);"," ","-\t\tif (ref.nonce) {","-\t\t\tthis._cachedNonces.set(ref.uri, ref.nonce);","-\t\t}","-\t\tthis._touchLru(ref.uri);","+\t\tthis._removeEntry(ref.uri, ref.nonce);","+\t\tthis._lru.push({ uri: ref.uri, nonce: ref.nonce ?? '' });","+","+\t\t// Try to clean up superseded nonces of this plugin; undeletable ones stay","+\t\t// in the LRU for a later attempt.","+\t\tawait this._cleanupStaleNoncesFor(ref.uri);"," \t\tawait this._evictIfNeeded();"," \t\tawait this._persistCache();"," ","@@ -126,31 +142,99 @@ export class AgentPluginManager implements IAgentPluginManager {"," \t}"," "," \tprivate _keyForUri(uri: string): string {","-\t\treturn uri.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/g, '-').replace(/-+/g, '-').replace(/^-|-$/g, '').substring(0, 128);","+\t\treturn this._sanitize(uri);","+\t}","+","+\tprivate _keyForNonce(nonce: string | undefined): string {","+\t\treturn (nonce && this._sanitize(nonce)) || 'default';","+\t}","+","+\tprivate _sanitize(value: string): string {","+\t\treturn value.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/g, '-').replace(/-+/g, '-').replace(/^-|-$/g, '').substring(0, 128);"," \t}"," ","-\tprivate _touchLru(uri: string): void {","-\t\tconst idx = this._lruOrder.indexOf(uri);","+\t/** Directory in which a specific `(uri, nonce)` revision is materialized. */","+\tprivate _dirFor(uri: string, nonce: string | undefined): URI {","+\t\treturn URI.joinPath(this._basePath, this._keyForUri(uri), this._keyForNonce(nonce));","+\t}","+","+\t/** Parent directory holding all materialized nonces of a plugin. */","+\tprivate _pluginRootFor(uri: string): URI {","+\t\treturn URI.joinPath(this._basePath, this._keyForUri(uri));","+\t}","+","+\tprivate _findEntry(uri: string, nonce: string | undefined): ICacheEntry | undefined {","+\t\tconst n = nonce ?? '';","+\t\treturn this._lru.find(entry => entry.uri === uri && entry.nonce === n);","+\t}","+","+\tprivate _removeEntry(uri: string, nonce: string | undefined): void {","+\t\tconst entry = this._findEntry(uri, nonce);","+\t\tif (entry) {","+\t\t\tthis._removeEntryRef(entry);","+\t\t}","+\t}","+","+\tprivate _removeEntryRef(entry: ICacheEntry): void {","+\t\tconst idx = this._lru.indexOf(entry);"," \t\tif (idx !== -1) {","-\t\t\tthis._lruOrder.splice(idx, 1);","+\t\t\tthis._lru.splice(idx, 1);","+\t\t}","+\t}","+","+\tprivate _touchLru(uri: string, nonce: string | undefined): void {","+\t\tconst entry = this._findEntry(uri, nonce);","+\t\tif (entry) {","+\t\t\tthis._removeEntryRef(entry);","+\t\t\tthis._lru.push(entry);","+\t\t}","+\t}","+","+\t/** Best-effort recursive delete; returns `true` only when the dir is gone. */","+\tprivate async _tryDeleteDir(dir: URI): Promise<boolean> {","+\t\ttry {","+\t\t\tawait this._fileService.del(dir, { recursive: true });","+\t\t\treturn true;","+\t\t} catch (err) {","+\t\t\tthis._logService.warn(`[AgentPluginManager] Failed to remove plugin dir ${dir.toString()}`, err);","+\t\t\treturn false;","+\t\t}","+\t}","+","+\t/** Attempts to evict older nonces of every tracked plugin. */","+\tprivate async _cleanupStaleNonces(): Promise<void> {","+\t\tfor (const uri of new Set(this._lru.map(entry => entry.uri))) {","+\t\t\tawait this._cleanupStaleNoncesFor(uri);","+\t\t}","+\t}","+","+\t/**","+\t * Attempts to evict every nonce of {@link uri} except the most recently used","+\t * one. Entries whose directory cannot be removed are left in the LRU so they","+\t * can be retried later, once whatever was holding them has released them.","+\t */","+\tprivate async _cleanupStaleNoncesFor(uri: string): Promise<void> {","+\t\tconst entries = this._lru.filter(entry => entry.uri === uri);","+\t\t// `entries` preserves LRU order; the last is the current revision.","+\t\tconst stale = entries.slice(0, -1);","+\t\tfor (const entry of stale) {","+\t\t\tthis._logService.info(`[AgentPluginManager] Evicting stale nonce for plugin: ${uri}`);","+\t\t\tif (await this._tryDeleteDir(this._dirFor(entry.uri, entry.nonce))) {","+\t\t\t\tthis._removeEntryRef(entry);","+\t\t\t}"," \t\t}","-\t\tthis._lruOrder.push(uri);"," \t}"," "," \tprivate async _evictIfNeeded(): Promise<void> {","-\t\twhile (this._lruOrder.length > this._maxPlugins) {","-\t\t\tconst evictUri = this._lruOrder.shift();","-\t\t\tif (!evictUri) {","+\t\twhile (this._lru.length > this._maxPlugins) {","+\t\t\tconst evicted = this._lru.shift();","+\t\t\tif (!evicted) {"," \t\t\t\tbreak;"," \t\t\t}","-\t\t\tthis._cachedNonces.delete(evictUri);","-\t\t\tconst evictKey = this._keyForUri(evictUri);","-\t\t\tconst evictDir = URI.joinPath(this._basePath, evictKey);","-\t\t\tthis._logService.info(`[AgentPluginManager] Evicting plugin: ${evictUri}`);","-\t\t\ttry {","-\t\t\t\tawait this._fileService.del(evictDir, { recursive: true });","-\t\t\t} catch (err) {","-\t\t\t\tthis._logService.warn(`[AgentPluginManager] Failed to evict plugin: ${evictUri}`, err);","+\t\t\tthis._logService.info(`[AgentPluginManager] Evicting plugin: ${evicted.uri}`);","+\t\t\tawait this._tryDeleteDir(this._dirFor(evicted.uri, evicted.nonce));","+\t\t\tif (!this._lru.some(entry => entry.uri === evicted.uri)) {","+\t\t\t\tawait this._tryDeleteDir(this._pluginRootFor(evicted.uri));"," \t\t\t}"," \t\t}"," \t}","@@ -176,26 +260,22 @@ export class AgentPluginManager implements IAgentPluginManager {"," \t\t\t// Entries are stored in LRU order (oldest first)"," \t\t\tfor (const entry of entries) {"," \t\t\t\tif (typeof entry.uri === 'string' && typeof entry.nonce === 'string') {","-\t\t\t\t\tthis._cachedNonces.set(entry.uri, entry.nonce);","-\t\t\t\t\tthis._lruOrder.push(entry.uri);","+\t\t\t\t\tthis._lru.push({ uri: entry.uri, nonce: entry.nonce });"," \t\t\t\t}"," \t\t\t}"," \t\t\tthis._logService.trace(`[AgentPluginManager] Loaded ${entries.length} cache entries from disk`);"," \t\t} catch (err) {"," \t\t\tthis._logService.warn('[AgentPluginManager] Failed to load cache from disk', err);"," \t\t}","+","+\t\tawait this._cleanupStaleNonces();","+\t\tawait this._persistCache();"," \t}"," "," \tprivate async _persistCache(): Promise<void> {"," \t\ttry {"," \t\t\t// Write entries in LRU order (oldest first)","-\t\t\tconst entries: ICacheEntry[] = [];","-\t\t\tfor (const uri of this._lruOrder) {","-\t\t\t\tconst nonce = this._cachedNonces.get(uri);","-\t\t\t\tif (nonce) {","-\t\t\t\t\tentries.push({ uri, nonce });","-\t\t\t\t}","-\t\t\t}","+\t\t\tconst entries: ICacheEntry[] = this._lru.map(entry => ({ uri: entry.uri, nonce: entry.nonce }));"," \t\t\tawait this._fileService.createFolder(this._basePath);"," \t\t\tawait this._fileService.writeFile(this._cachePath, VSBuffer.fromString(JSON.stringify(entries)));"," \t\t} catch (err) {"],"additions":126,"deletions":46,"truncated":false},{"path":"src/vs/platform/agentHost/node/copilot/copilotAgentSession.ts","lines":["@@ -2170,10 +2170,7 @@ export class CopilotAgentSession extends Disposable {"," \t\t// plugin-derived child (narrow `SessionMcpServerStateChanged`) or a"," \t\t// bare top-level entry (`SessionCustomizationUpdated`)."," \t\tthis._register(wrapper.onMcpServersLoaded(e => {","-\t\t\tconst servers = e.data.servers","-\t\t\t\t.map(s => this._toSdkMcpServer(s.name, s.status, s.error))","-\t\t\t\t.filter(isDefined);","-\t\t\tthis._mcpCustomizations.applyAll(servers);","+\t\t\tthis._applyMcpServerList(e.data.servers);"," \t\t}));"," \t\tthis._register(wrapper.onMcpServerStatusChanged(e => {"," \t\t\tconst server = this._toSdkMcpServer(e.data.serverName, e.data.status, e.data.error);","@@ -2187,6 +2184,37 @@ export class CopilotAgentSession extends Disposable {"," \t\